	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You chant the names of several animals and your body distorts in a grotesque way as it changes shape and you assume a different form.</em></p><p><strong>Utility</strong></p><p>You change your appearance. You decide what you look like, including your facial features, hair length, height, weight, sex, skin color, sound of your voice, etc. You can't appear as a size other than medium or small, and you can't gain extra limbs or other body parts, and you can't gain any extra abilities. While this spell lasts, you can change your appearance as an action.</p><p>While transformed you gain one of the following, which can only be swapped by casting this spell again:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Natural Weapons:</strong> Your @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.pRDNsHpNLLk1Qq58]{unarmed strikes} are replaced with a natural weapon of your choice, such as claws, horns, or hooves.</p><ul><li><p>You are proficient with this natural weapon, and use your spellcasting ability modifier for attack and damage bonuses.</p></li><li><p>The natural weapon deals [[/damage 1d6 type=bludgeoning/piercing/slashing]] damage, as appropriate to the natural weapon you chose.</p></li><li><p>It has a 5 ft. range, is magic, and you have a +1 bonus to the attack and damage rolls you make using it.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Aquatic Adaptation:</strong> You adapt your body to an aquatic environment, sprouting gills and growing webbing between your fingers. You can breathe underwater and gain a &amp;reference[swimming]{Swimming} speed equal to your walking speed.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
